        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 1:28AM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 128 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from San Patricio to near Premont. Movement was
southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kingsville, Alice, Robstown, Driscoll, Bishop, Ricardo, Alfred-South
La Paloma, Bluntzer, Banquete, San Jose, Ben Bolt, Palito Blanco,
Tecalote, Annaville, Alice Acres, Alfred, Calallen, Kingsville Naval
Air Station, Agua Dulce, and North San Pedro.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 37 between mile markers 12 and 15.
US Highway 281 between mile markers 660 and 698.
US Highway 77 between mile markers 672 and 700.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 200 AM CDT for
south central Texas.</instruction>
